msItem.note:
Fragment of “The Anaphora of the Three Hundred”, repeated 16 times, with different musical notation and different headings: Za-sanuy “Of Monday”; 
                           Za-rabuʿ  “Of Wednesday”; Za-ʿārb “Of Friday”; Za-qadām “Of Saturday”; Za-ʾǝhud “Of Sunday”; Zäwätǝr “Of every day”; Za-9 baʿālat “Of nine feasts”; Za-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝna Māryām “Of Our Lady Mary”; Za-nabiyāt  “Of the prophets”; Za-ḥawāryāt “Of the Apostles”;
                           ʿƎzl “(Mode of chant)”; Za-ṣadqan “Of the righteous”; Za-samaʿ ǝtāt “Of the martyrs”; Za-malāʾǝkt “Of the angels”; Arārāy “(Mode of chant)”; Za-kirubel  “Of Cherubs”
